            "comment": "Jasper Douglas-Bloodmoon — Intimacy Baseline",
            "content": "Fundamentally, Jasper seeks intimacy as a release valve for the crushing pressure of his cyber-war against his family and the unspoken guilt of his mother's death. His baseline attraction leans heavily into high-stimulation and hyper-attentive control/release. Because his entire life is about breaking rules and hiding in the shadows, he wants intimacy to be loud, defiant, and undeniable. Intimacy, to him, is a shared rebellion where he can strip away his sarcastic tech-armor and exist genuinely, entirely focused on his partner's reactions.",
